texts.text: The weak must not prevail!
*Roar*
*Wince*
>Sabaoth roars as it lets loose an overwhelming shout.
>You all try to fight it, but are brought to your knees.
Hey, I can't move...
It seriously just paralyzed us with a single shout?
Yo, it'll wipe us out if we're not careful...
But this world's dependin' on us.
We ain't backin' down here. Not now...!
Fight me if you can.
Prove your power to me!
Ain't gotta tell us that twice!
Yo, Newbie, can you stand?!
Of course!
Let's beat it already!
Aight!
Let's do this! Devil Download!
>The Liberators rise back up and prepare to fight Sabaoth.
>They get into position and begin attacking.
>But Sabaoth remains untouched.
>Nothing appears to be working regardless of how many times you attack.
No, that will not be enough!
Show me your power!
*Wince*
*Pant*
I guess the "Lord of the Armies" isn't just another lame title.
Megakin, our chances of winning will only decrease the longer this fight continues.
We need to end this soon...!
Aight, looks like we ain't got any other choice...
Newbie, we'll give it another salvo.
You give it everything you've got once we get its attention, got it?
We ain't got enough left in the tank for a marathon battle.
You're only gonna get a small window to attack,
but we promise to give you that chance!
I believe in you, Newbie. I know you can do it.
And I'm sure the rest of you feel the same way.
Yes, we do!
You've accomplished so many great things already!
Leave it to me.
O-Okay, I get it...
That's our Newbie!

*Chuckle*
I meant every word of that!
Aight, Liberators, let's do this! One more time!
>Their demons all prepare to launch another attack!
>They attack Sabaoth relentlessly with no sign of stopping.
The act of a desperate foot soldier flailing his sword about.
They may be dangerous when backed into a corner,
but oblivion is what ultimately awaits them...
This appears to be the end.
Yo, don't write us off yet...!
Go!
*Roar*
>Megakin's demon draws Sabaoth's attention.
Newbie, now!
>You jump out and charge in front of Sabaoth.
*Howl*
You...
>Your attack hits Sabaoth!
*Roar*
It worked!
Nice one, Newbie!
Hey, Sabaoth's acting all weird now!
>It appears that way...
>But Sabaoth returns to normal soon after.
Yo, hold up. It didn't work at all?
You gotta be kiddin' me...
I didn't think it was serious about going one versus all, but nothing's working...
How the hell are we supposed to win?
I'm really not sure...
No, it's too soon for that...!
We ain't givin' up here!
All these folks are countin' on us! We can't lose here!
We can't give up!!
You wish to protect this world...?
Well, duh!
You aim to see your fight against Vanitas through to the end?
Why do you care all the sudden?!
Yo, I don't know what your angle is, but FYI, we're fightin' against you too.
We ain't lettin' you and your friends lay waste to our world!
He's right! Even if it means losing our ability to summon demons.
We will keep fighting as long there is someone that needs our help!
>You and the others nod in agreement and stand back up!
So be it...

Liberators.
You may pass.
And this world shall be spared from being erased.
What...?
We... We won?
Yo, really?!
There is no lie in the word of God.
No way... Awesome!
Not so fast, Sabaoth.
As supreme lord of the bestowing of life, I, Shaddai, cannot allow this to pass.
Huh?
Shaddai?
This trial does not serve as a true test of faith.
And these humans have become dangerous. They pose a threat to God.
They cannot be allowed to exist.
H-Hold on, Shaddai!
What are you talking about? What do you mean we're a threat to God...?
Liberators.
You were in a position to wish for God's salvation during your battle against Elohim.
Yet you chose to find a way to win without praying.
Win...? Yo, Vince and Honey beat it?!
T-They did it!
What a relief...
So what's your problem exactly?
We'll give you that you're not really on our side,
but you definitely gave us the impression that you weren't against what we were doing.
Indeed.
If you lost to Elohim, then I would have let you all be.
However, this now has to do with the correct relationship between God and his children.
Correct relationship?
In order to overcome the test that was Elohim,
you were to pray to God for his help.
That was the correct way to behave. That was how your faith was to be tested.
Well, too bad.
Because it sounds like Vince and Honey did away with Elohim just fine by themselves.
Befriending an abomination, that Homunculus, in such a manner.
It is pure blasphemy.
Yo, that's what our trial was, right? TO beat Elohim!
And what's wrong with workin' together?!
How does that make us a threat to God?
Don't you get it?
Creating life is supposed to be something only God can do.
But humanity crossed the line by doing just that.
Homunculi, artificial humans, aren't allowed to exist.
On top of that, our Homunculus partnered up with an actual person,
and managed to win against a Godly spirit.
Of course they hate us now.
Hey, eyeball, what's got you so pissed off all of a sudden?
Is God really that small-minded?
Vince?! Honey?!
Thank goodness you're safe...!
I said we'd take care of things, right?
Anyway, it looks like we came back at a good time.
Yo, that's an understatement.
Shaddai.
We don't care what anyone says. We're all friends here.
And anyone who shares the same goals as us is welcome to join us.
We ain't in the business of discrminatin'.
Yo, that's what our dogma, "Fellowship," is all about.
Real connections.
And we're gonna use these connections to do somethin' about Vanitas.
Yo, I'm sure we can. I know we can!

Fellowship...
Helping others, forging bonds, love...
That is very commendable and righteous of you.
However...
You still do not seem to understand.
Those ideas all exist because God made it so.
>Shaddai's power increases dramatically.
I was hoping that you would become the true saviors of this world.
But you have shunned God's love by doing what is forbidden.
Pure blasphemy.
Elohim's defeat now serves as a harbinger for things to come.
So now, you must face judgment.
Perish before God!
